property.name: message
property.value: "You know this dainty monster, too, it seems, hypocrite adventurer!"

property.name: message
property.value: "You again. Far more than Life, The subtle bonds of Death around us twine."

property.name: message
property.value: "Thou givest me the beauty of divine caresses. Without pity or mercy we will fight."

property.name: message
property.value: "Oh. I cannot like a love-leaf wantonly Consign this stunted monster to the glowing grate."

property.name: message
property.value: "Oh cursed be that transient night of vain desire When I conceived my expiation in my womb!"

property.name: message
property.value: "Ah, why did I not bear a serpent's nest entire, Instead of bringing forth this hideous Child of Doom!"

property.name: message
property.value: "As an unfathomed sphinx, enthroned by the Nile, My heart a swan's whiteness with granite combines."

property.name: message
property.value: "The panting swain that o'er his mistress sighs, Seems the Sick, that stroke their gravestones lovingly."

property.name: message
property.value: "I advance to attack, and I climb to assault, Like a swarm of maggots after a cadaver."

property.name: message
property.value: "The thunder and the rain have made such ravage My garden is nigh bare of rosy fruit."

property.name: message
property.value: "Rembrandt, gloomy hospital filled with murmuring, Ornamented only with a large crucifix."

property.name: message
property.value: "Far from famous sepulchers Toward a lonely cemetery My heart Goes beating funeral marches."

property.name: message
property.value: "You could count in your beds More kisses than fleurs-de-lis And subject to your power Many Valois!"

property.name: message
property.value: "My spirit resembles the tower which crumbles Under the tireless blows of the battering ram."

property.name: message
property.value: "Kisses and bite, Tortures the breast of an old witch. Steal as we pass by a clandestine pleasure."

property.name: message
property.value: "I should have loved to have lived Beside a maiden giantess, Like a luxurious cat at the feet of a queen."

property.name: message
property.value: "In days when Christian seeds bloomed o'er the land, the monk Exalted Death in rude and simple way."

property.name: message
property.value: "Come, superb cat. My hand tingles with the pleasure Of feeling your electric body."

property.name: message
property.value: "Angel of gaiety, have you known anguish, Shame and remorse, tears, boredom, and dismay?"

property.name: message
property.value: "Tight, swarming, like a million worms, A population of Demons carries on in our brains."

property.name: message
property.value: "The Demon makes secret holes in this abyss, Whence would escape a thousand years of sweat and strain."

property.name: message
property.value: "The Living Torches, they save, Towards the Path of Joy they guide my ways."

property.name: message
property.value: "When by an edict of the powers supreme A poet's born into this world's drab space."

property.name: message
property.value: "His mother starts, in horror, to blaspheme Clenching her fists at God, who grants her grace."

property.name: message
property.value: "Poets, before my grandiose poses, Will consume their lives in austere study."

property.name: message
property.value: "I was 6 when verses stopped blooming in the fields like roses."

property.name: message
property.value: "In her grief, The Mother, chaste and thin, was Near her treacherous spouse who was once her lover. "

property.name: message
property.value: "Obeying a curious whim, I had banned studies from that spectacle."

property.name: message
property.value: "Sweltering Africa and languorous Asia, A whole far-away world, absent, almost defunct."

property.name: message
property.value: "Disease and Death make ashes Of all the fire that flamed for us."

property.name: message
property.value: "He smokes his hookah, while he dreams Of gibbets, weeping tears he cannot smother. "

property.name: message
property.value: "This world will soon end, at the foot of the delicious terrible catafalque."

property.name: message
property.value: "I was happy, healthy, and sated; As for me, my arms are weary Because I have embraced the clouds."
